Thus was the work of the person of Cali who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A dactyloscopist from Cali went to history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano'.
The work of these officials is crucial.
Last November 4 a Dactyloscope of the Cali CTI went to history as the person who confirmed the identity of the Supreme Chief of the Farc: "Alfonso Cano", comparing his fingerprints.
Seven dactyloscopes working in the ITC's local offices this week were the "available" tour of Eliaszar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the field of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Choco, where he had to spend more than five days in the forest to reach the place where the bodies were to be identified.
In 2000 he was transferred to the capital of Valle and after having followed appropriate courses, he specializes in dactyloscopy, which is the study of friction skin, i.e. the thumbs and feet.
During the week of the operation against Alfonso Cano alias, Eleazar was warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter in Palmira.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected of being the man who led the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to take the card with the ten digital prints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigation team at the site of the body, he did not recognize it physically, because it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He had no beard, he was dressed as a peasant of the area, without glasses and much more left.
But the prints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian wolf, the Incre, a picker and a lantern, Eleazar compared the body's digital prints to those on the map.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was responsible for confirming to the Minister of Defence Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the Supreme Chief of the Farc.
Looking for the print
For a dactyloscope of Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eleazar González at a press conference for the operation against "Cano" is very significant.
A lot of people don't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an accurate science, without a margin of error, which can be crucial in the resolution of crimes.
In addition to identifying the bodies, dactyloscopists support investigations for crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many criminals have false identity cards or no documents.
We take their digital prints and search the database.
The researcher said that in a case of theft he had to remove a part of the wall from a house, because in this place the thief had leaned his hand to get out a chest full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to draw a digital print, but in this case we were able to get the print from the whole hand and identify the offender who had participated in various flights," he recalls.
Prints may also remove or confirm suspects in cases of homicide.
Recently we found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
Through the investigation, it was determined that a parent could be suspected of crime and indeed a printing on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that he is the killer, it places him on the scene of the crime.
A CTI dactyloscope explained that "the digital prints of objects were extracted with chemical or physical reactives".
When they appear, a lift or a band is used to pick them up.
Later, the prints are sent to Asif, the decommissioning database, or to the National Civil Registry.
"The problem is that there are still a lot of undocumented Colombians," the ITC expert said.
He explained that everything is not how we show it in the CSI TV program.
Since everything that shines isn't gold, all we touch isn't necessarily a print.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is achieved.
